The paper deals with optimization problems related to vectors and spheres, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of multiplicative weights-based algorithms and lower bounds also suggests categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the mention of covering a Gaussian random variable suggests a connection to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
